#Text=Kupang
#Text=Kupang is a city in West Timor and the provincial capital of East Nusa Tenggara .
#Text=By plane
#Text=El Tari International Airport ( KOE Bandar Udara El Tari ) , Jl .
#Text=Adi Sucipto , ☏ +62274484261 .
#Text=Has services to Surabaya , Denpasar , Jakarta , Maumere , Ende and many other remote regions in East Nusa Tenggara .
#Text=Air Timor has services to Dili three times per week .
#Text=There is a ' Coco Taxi ' operating .
#Text=A trip from airport to town should be IDR 50,000-80,000.
#Text=By bus
#Text=Kupang is a 12-hour bus ride away from Dili , East Timor .
#Text=Soé is a 3 hour bus ride .
#Text=Get around
#Text=You can use " Microbus " ( locally called bemo ) .
#Text=The uniqueness of public transportation in the city of Kupang is due to the appearance filled with accessories , decorations and music blaring .
#Text=Each bemo is manned by a driver and an assistant who collects the money from passengers .
#Text=You can tell the assistant your destination / drop-off point in advance .
#Text=There are multiple routes , so you need to ask your accommodations if any of the bemos are are passing by your destinations .
#Text=Within Kupang the route number can be seen on top of the bemo , whereas for further destination , it will write the destination name .
#Text=Each trip is IDR 3,000 ( as of Dec 2018 ) .
#Text=Ride-hailing app such as Grab and Go-Jek is getting more popular here , but you may need to wait a little bit more as the number of drivers are still growing ( as of Dec 2018 ) .
#Text=See
#Text=Lasiana Beach ( Pantai Lasiana ) .
#Text=Famous for its white sand .
#Text=There are n't many buildings , so you can enjoy the natural beach .
#Text=Do
#Text=If you like loud music , you can try " Diskotek Berjalan " style of Kupang .

column1: #Text=Roslin Orphanage , Kupang ( Timor ) .
#Text=If you are in Kupang a visit to the Roslin Orphanage is a definite must .
#Text=Google and youtube " Roslin Orphanage " for more information .
#Text=Peggy and Budi Soehardi are CNN heroes and once you read about their story , you will understand why .
#Text=There were some controversies about their volunteers recently , but just go there and decide for yourself .
#Text=Waterpark Kupang , Jl .
#Text=WJ Lalamentik .
#Text=A water-amusement park .
#Text=Buy
#Text=Oeba Market ( Pasar Oeba ) ( Bemo #6 , #10 passing by this market . ) .
#Text=A traditional market next to a pier selling daily needs .
#Text=Tourists will receive a moderate attention here .
#Text=Flobamora Mall , Jl .
#Text=WJ Lalamentik .
#Text=The largest mall in area is the Ramayana Department Store which includes shops , food courts , games and other facilities .
#Text=Flobamora Mall is a family mall concept to provide all the needs of the family in one place .
#Text=Hypermart Kupang , Jl .
#Text=El Tari II Bundaran PU , ☏ +623808585060 .
#Text=Lippo Plaza Fatululi .
#Text=two-floor shopping center with Matahari Dept Store and Hypermarket .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Restoran
#Text=Nelayan
#Text=, Jl .
#Text=Timor Raya 14 , ☏ +62380823000 .
#Text=Beachside restaurant with lots of choices including seafood .
#Text=You can enjoy this dish in huts on the seafront
#Text=Restoran Teluk Kupang , Jl .
#Text=Timor Raya , ☏ +62380822757 .
#Text=Also beachside restaurant which served delicious seafood .
#Text=Grilled Banana in Lasiana Beach .
#Text=Here you can eat grilled banana with a variety of flavors while enjoying the beautiful beach and the sound of waves
#Text=for Jagung Bose : along the sidewalk on the Jalan El Tari ( in front of the Governor 's office ) .
#Text=for Se'i Babi : ' Depot Bambu Kuning ' and ' Se'i Babi Aroma ' ( two branches ) are the two most popular places to have Se'i Babi .
#Text=Night Market ( Pasar Malam ) :
#Text=Every night there is a street food market centred around Jalan Kosasih , not far from the shore .
#Text=The stalls fry up lots of fresh seafood - fish , lobsters , crabs , etc. , while the tahu tempe penyet is a great vegetarian option .
#Text=Next to the food stalls are drinks stations where the best options are the fresh juice .
#Text=Juice avokap ( avocado juice ) and jus naga ( dragonfruit juice ) are especially common and are blended with ice , sugar , and sweetened condensed milk/chocolate syrup .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Kelimutu Hotel , Jalan Gunung Meja .
#Text=Check-out : 1pm .
#Text=A three-storey hotel that has seen better days .
#Text=However , private rooms with bathrooms and AC are available for a good price .
#Text=It 's not far from the central bus terminal and the night street food market .
#Text=The staff are friendly though no English is spoken .
#Text=Free tea and coffee in the morning .
#Text=Free Wifi is available around the reception area .
#Text=Standard fan Rp100,000 , Standard AC Rp125,000 , Deluxe AC Rp150,000 .
#Text=Lavalon Hostel , ☏ +628123770533 .

#Text=A backpacker spot with a friendly English-speaking staff , who will answer any question about flights , buses and ferries , flyers and maps on other hostels in Roti and East Timor , and is a good place to meet other backpackers with whom you can talk and share information .
#Text=Dorm IDR 70,000 ; Fan IDR 160,000 ; A/C IDR 260,000 .
#Text=SwissBel Inn Kristal , Jl .
#Text=Timor Raya 59 , ☏ +62380825100 .

#Text=A three-star international hotel in the heart of Kupang , 20 minutes from El Tari Airport , the hotel allows easy access to the business and government district as well as some of the most noteworthy sites in the vicinity .
#Text=T-More Hotel , Jl .
#Text=Piet A. Tallo , ☏ +62380881555 .
#Text=Three-star hotel with the concept of transit and business .
#Text=Go next
#Text=Soe : the highland area to visit traditional village in Boti and None .
#Text=3 hours .
#Text=First take the bemo to ' Noelbakul ' destination , and then stop at Oesapa " bus stop " .
#Text=You can find " Travel " shared car for IDR 50,000 or bus for IDR 30,000 ( Bus to Kefamenanu will pass by Soe too , ask the bus assistant ) .
#Text=Dili ( East Timor / Timor Leste ) : No ferry from Kupang to Dili is running as of January 22 , 2012 .
#Text=The most common way to go to Dili is via land ( 12 hours ) .
#Text=Flight route of Kupang-Dili is available in 2018 .
#Text=( Note : As of May 26 , 2015 , all EU passport holders ( except Ireland or UK ) no longer need a visa to East Timor .
#Text=Otherwise , for all nationalities except Indonesian , a free ' Visa Authorisation Letter ' must be obtained from the East Timorese Consulate prior to reaching the land border ) .
